OL,3,CWould-be parents 'delay having
OL,4,Cchildren because of cost-of-living
OL,5,Ccrisis'
OL,7,FIncreases in the cost of living are
OL,8,Fcausing people to put off having
OL,9,Fchildren, according to research, as a
OL,10,Fgrowing number say rising prices are
OL,11,Faffecting how they plan their families.
OL,13,FA survey of more than 4,000 people by
OL,14,Finsurer Royal London found that 22% of
OL,15,Fpeople aged 18 to 34 have made changes
OL,16,Fto family planning because of the
OL,17,Fcrisis.
