OL,3,CWould-be parents 'delay having
OL,4,Cchildren because of cost-of-living
OL,5,Ccrisis'
OL,7,FMeanwhile, 8% of people in the age
OL,8,Fbracket said they have delayed having
OL,9,Fchildren because they do not have the
OL,10,Fmoney.
OL,12,FThe research found that worsening
OL,13,Feconomic conditions mean the average
OL,14,Ffamily with young children has seen
OL,15,Fexpenses rise by more than #1,000 a
OL,16,Fmonth.
OL,18,FAs a result, 18% of parents questioned
OL,19,Fsaid they have been left with no money
OL,20,Ffor unexpected bills or emergencies.
